NGUYỄN THÀNH LONG is an Intern/Fresher AI Engineer with a strong academic foundation in Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and Natural Language Processing. Their core expertise lies in developing advanced AI solutions leveraging Transformer-based architectures, CNNs, and LSTMs. Through academic and personal projects, they have designed a Visual Question Answering (VQA) system combining CNN and Transformer, achieving 78% accuracy on the COCO-VQA dataset and optimizing model inference speed by 25%. They also fine-tuned a GPT-3 model for Neural Machine Translation, achieving a BLEU score of 32 after preprocessing 50,000 sentence pairs, and developed an Image Captioning system with an encoder-decoder CNN-LSTM model, yielding a BLEU-4 score of 0.65 on Flickr8k. Further experience includes building an OCR pipeline for scanned documents with image preprocessing for over 1,000 documents and applying machine learning models like XGBoost, Random Forest, and Linear Regression for Real Estate Price Prediction, achieving an R2 score of 0.89 with SHAP for interpretability.
Technically, NGUYỄN THÀNH LONG is proficient in Python, Java, JavaScript, and SQL. Their hands-on technical stack includes deep learning frameworks such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras, and HuggingFace Transformers, alongside data science libraries like Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, and Seaborn. They have experience with MLOps tools like Streamlit and FastAPI for model deployment, version control with Git, and Linux environments. Domain knowledge spans Multimodal Learning, Sequence Modeling, Time Series Forecasting, Text Summarization, Sentiment Analysis, Data Visualization, and advanced data preprocessing techniques including ColumnTransformer, Imputation, Scaling, and Encoding. They also possess skills in Top-K High Utility Itemset Mining, Depth-first search (DFS), and pruning strategies, complemented by certifications in Advanced Computer Vision, Neural Networks, Deep Learning, and Time Series Forecasting.